                        <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                            <strong>Qehwexane</strong> (caf√©s) are essential to Kurdish social life. Men traditionally gather at caf√©s to drink tea, play games, and discuss news. Modern caf√©s now welcome everyone and serve as workspaces and meeting places. Tea (<strong>√ßay</strong>) is the drink of choice, served in small glasses. Spending hours at a caf√© is normal and expected - rushing is not part of the culture.
                        </p>
